Impostors brings a breath of fresh air into the gaming and crypto world by creating a social gaming metaverse that is truly player-owned and powered.

asset_contract.description:
The MonsterBuds Genesis Collection consists of 10,420 Generation 1 MonsterBuds and 865 Puff Puff Passes. 

Generation 1 MonsterBuds are the center of the DankVerse and the key to earning in our P2E Smoke Session game. Generation 1 MonsterBuds will also generate $DANK, the utility token for the DankVerse. Each MonsterBud initially had two breed counts. When purchasing, make sure to verify each Bud's breed count using its token ID on [monsterbuds.io](https://monsterbuds.io). 

The Puff Puff Pass is our utility pass for the DankVerse. Originally given to our early supporters for presale access, we've since utilized our Puff Puff Pass as a utility NFT, giving a number of premium benefits including NFT claims, software access, presale spots, and VIP access to exclusive events and giveaways.

asset.description:
Swinging through the metaverse with 8,444 apes in 2022, Apes R Us features bold, fun and unique NFTs to match your personality and style. Our apes encompass everyday traits along with some of your favourite characters you may have loved over the years of growing up.
The artwork that we have created is purely hand-drawn illustrations by Katun, a popular graffiti artist based in Malaysia that has stretched his wings globally over the last couple of years. He has worked with renowned artists such as Chris Brown, Dua Lipa, Post Malone and has also worked with brands such as Vans, Marshall, Footlocker, KFC, Oppo and many more. 
Joining our community means more than just art, it also provides community-based exclusive access to many portals throughout our roadmap that you will be able to unlock as we move forward and we’re excited to see each and every one of you join our journey.

The artwork that we have created is purely hand-drawn illustrations by Katun, a popular graffiti artist based in Malaysia that has stretched his wings globally over the last couple of years. He has worked with renowned artists such as Chris Brown, Dua Lipa, Post Malone and has also worked with brands such as Vans, Marshall, Footlocker, KFC, Oppo and many more. 

Joining our community means more than just art, it also provides community-based exclusive access to many portals throughout our roadmap that you will be able to unlock as we move forward and we’re excited to see each and every one of you join our journey.

Dotdotdots are strange cultish creatures that live inside solidity. They disguise themselves as decimals in the code and are rarely seen naturally by human eyes. They are often referred to as bugs, but their species is unknown.

Dotdotsdots can be minted directly from the contract using the mint function with a price of 0.05 ETH, up to a max of 5 per transaction. There will be 4360 dotdotdots initially for mint, but will increase as the all time high price of Ethereum rises, with a cap of 10,000.

asset.description:
Painted by Register

Painting Specs: 90” W x 57” H, on Canvas. Medium: Acrylic, Oil Stick, Mixed Media.

NFT Specs: 3828 x 2339, 26.9 MB, PNG. Edition Size 17. 

Purple haze all in my brain lately. Things just don't seem the same, actin’ funny but I don't know why. ‘Scuse me while I kiss the sky. Purple haze all around, don't know if I'm coming up or down. Am I happy or in misery? Whatever it is, that girl put a spell on me. Purple haze all in my eyes. Don't know if it's day or night. You got me blowing, blowing my mind. Is it tomorrow or just the end of time?

Jimi Hendrix
asset.name: EXCUSE ME WHILE I KISS THE SKY #12/17

collection.name: Register Collection
collection.description:
Register's Custom BAYC Paintings - https://opensea.io/collection/register

Register came into the NFT scene in early 2021 doing custom paintings of Bored Ape Yacht Club Apes and various other custom creations of Personal Profile Pictures. Here is the collection of his own images, mostly using acrylic paint and oil stick on large canvases balancing chaos and harmony.

“Excuse Me Wile I Kiss The Sky” released on 8/31/2021 is a tribute to musical inspiration from Jimi Hendrix. Music and art are tightly woven together in Register’s world. This collection is from a painting 8 feet wide and was completed in December of 2020. The lips will be the key to get access first to Register's future drops.

For custom work or to contact Register: @registerartist registerartist@gmail.com 

For more info visit: https://registerartist.com
